Win.Packed.Azorult-10005443-0.description: Azorult is a banking trojan that attempts to steal credit card data and other sensitive information to facilitate cybercrime.

Win.Packed.Dridex-10005543-1.description: Dridex is a well-known banking trojan that aims to steal credentials and other sensitive information from an infected machine.

Win.Packed.Redline-10005632-0.description: Redline Stealer is an information-stealer written in .NET and sold on hacking forums.

Win.Packed.Upatre-10005147-0.description: Upatre is a malicious downloader often used by exploit kits and phishing campaigns. It downloads and executes malicious executables, such as banking malware.

Win.Packed.Zusy-10005219-0.description: Zusy, also known as TinyBanker or Tinba, is a trojan that uses man-in-the-middle attacks to steal banking information. When executed, it injects itself into legitimate Windows processes such as "explorer.exe" and "winver.exe." When the user accesses a banking website, it displays a form to trick the user into submitting personal information.

Win.Packed.njRAT-10005525-1.description: njRAT, also known as Bladabindi, is a remote access trojan (RAT) that allows attackers to execute commands on the infected host, log keystrokes and remotely turn on the victim's webcam and microphone. njRAT was developed by the Sparclyheason group. Some of the largest attacks using this malware date back to 2014.

Win.Virus.Xpiro-10005555-1.description: Expiro is a known file infector and information-stealer that hinders analysis with anti-debugging and anti-analysis tricks.

Win.Worm.Vobus-10005311-1.description: Vobus is a worm that spreads itself through removable drives. Once installed, Vobus will often download and execute additional malware.
